{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886220491,"sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1138aa0011n6B7cjiBdGpUy","messageID":"msg_d7b1124fd001TMLIipQz14HW06","sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_279a8fd37c664517879f5146","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n2: \n3: **Module:** example\n4: **Language:** Python\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube Python SDK 提供一个 PCAP（Packet Capture）网络流量分析示例应用，展示如何使用 `CodeInterpreterClient` 在远程沙箱环境中完成文件上传、代码执行、结果下载的完整工作流。该示例覆盖 SDK 的核心 API（`upload_file`、`run_code`、`execute_command`、`download_file`、context manager 生命周期），为用户提供一个可运行的网络分析参考实现，降低 SDK 上手门槛。\n10: \n11: ## Scope\n12: \n13: ### In Scope\n14: \n15: 1. **示例脚本** `examples/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n16:    - 环境变量配置（`ROUTER_URL`、`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`、`AUTH_TOKEN`）\n17:    - PCAP 文件上传至远程沙箱（`upload_file`）\n18:    - 使用 `run_code` 执行 Python 分析脚本（基于 `scapy` 库）：\n19:      - 协议分布统计（TCP/UDP/ICMP/HTTP/DNS 占比）\n20:      - Top N 源/目的 IP 地址\n21:      - 流量时间线概览\n22:    - 使用 `execute_command` 运行 shell 命令（如 `tshark` 过滤，如可用）\n23:    - 分析结果下载（`download_file`，JSON/CSV 格式）\n24:    - Context manager 模式演示完整的创建-使用-清理生命周期\n25: \n26: 2. **辅助文件**\n27:    - `examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md` — 运行指南、前置条件、预期输出\n28:    - `examples/pcap_analyzer/requirements.txt` — 示例依赖（scapy）\n29:    - `examples/pcap_analyzer/sample_traffic.pcap` — 小体积示例 PCAP 文件（< 1MB）\n30: \n31: 3. **SDK API 覆盖**\n32:    - `CodeInterpreterClient` context manager（`__enter__`/`__exit__`）\n33:    - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n34:    - `run_code(language, code)`\n35:    - `execute_command(command)`\n36:    - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`\n37:    - `list_files(path)`\n38:    - `stop()` 清理\n39: \n40: ### Out of Scope\n41: \n42: - PCAP 文件的实时捕获功能（仅分析已有文件）\n43: - Web UI 或可视化界面（纯 CLI 示例）\n44: - 修改 SDK 核心代码（仅使用 `agentcube` 公开 API）\n45: - `AgentRuntimeClient` 的使用（由 `agent_runtime_usage.py` 覆盖）\n46: - 大文件分片上传（示例使用 < 1MB 文件）\n47: - 异步 I/O 版本的 SDK 调用\n48: \n49: ## Architecture Summary\n50: \n51: ### Current State\n52: \n53: - `examples/` 目录下已有 `basic_usage.py` 和 `agent_runtime_usage.py` 两个示例\n54: - 缺少一个覆盖文件操作 + 代码执行 + 结果下载的完整端到端示例\n55: - 用户难以直观理解如何在沙箱中处理实际文件分析场景\n56: \n57: ### Target State\n58: \n59: ```\n60: examples/pcap_analyzer/\n61: ├── pcap_analyzer.py       # 主示例脚本\n62: ├── README.md              # 运行指南\n63: ├── requirements.txt       # 示例依赖\n64: └── sample_traffic.pcap    # 示例 PCAP 文件\n65: ```\n66: \n67: **执行流程**：\n68: \n69: ```\n70: ┌──────────┐    upload_file     ┌─────────────────┐\n71: │  Local   │ ─────────────────▶ │  Remote Sandbox │\n72: │  PCAP    │                    │  /tmp/capture   │\n73: │  File    │                    └────────┬────────┘\n74: └──────────┘                           │\n75:                                        │ run_code (scapy analysis)\n76:                                        │ execute_command (tshark filter)\n77:                                        ▼\n78:                               ┌─────────────────┐\n79:                               │  Analysis       │\n80:                               │  Results (JSON) │\n81:                               └────────┬────────┘\n82:                                        │\n83:                           download_file │\n84:                                        ▼\n85: ┌──────────┐                    ┌─────────────────┐\n86: │  Local   │ ◀───────────────── │  Remote Sandbox │\n87: │  Report  │                    │  /tmp/report    │\n88: │  (JSON)  │                    └─────────────────┘\n89: └──────────┘\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ## Impact Analysis\n93: \n94: ### Dependencies\n95: \n96: | 依赖 | 来源 | 说明 |\n97: |------|------|------|\n98: | `agentcube-sdk` | 本地 | `CodeInterpreterClient`（`upload_file`、`run_code`、`execute_command`、`download_file`） |\n99: | `scapy` | 远程沙箱 | PCAP 解析库（在沙箱中通过 `run_code` 安装或使用） |\n100: | `tshark`（可选） | 远程沙箱 | 命令行过滤工具 |\n101: \n102: ### Affected Components\n103: \n104: | 文件/目录 | 状态 | 说明 |\n105: |-----------|------|------|\n106: | `examples/pcap_analyzer/` | 新增 | 示例应用完整目录 |\n107: | `python-sdk/` | 无变更 | 作为依赖被引用 |\n108: \n109: ### Risk Assessment\n110: \n111: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n112: |------|------|----------|\n113: | 远程沙箱缺少 `scapy` 库 | 中 | 示例脚本中通过 `run_code` 执行 `pip install scapy` 预安装 |\n114: | PCAP 文件过大导致上传超时 | 低 | 提供 < 1MB 示例文件，文档中说明大文件处理建议 |\n115: | 沙箱环境差异导致脚本行为不一致 | 中 | 示例使用纯 Python `scapy`，避免系统级依赖 |\n116: | 示例代码与 SDK API 变更不同步 | 低 | 仅使用公开 API（`__all__` 导出），API 变更时同步更新 |\n117: \n118: ## Alternatives Considered\n119: \n120: ### 1. 纯 `scapy` vs. `tshark`/`pyshark` 组合（✅ 选定纯 scapy）\n121: \n122: - **纯 scapy**：纯 Python 实现，无需系统级依赖，跨平台兼容性好\n123: - **tshark/pyshark**：解析能力更强，但需要系统安装 Wireshark/tshark\n124: - **决策**：以 `scapy` 为主，`tshark` 作为可选增强（条件检测）\n125: \n126: ### 2. CLI 脚本 vs. FastAPI Web 服务（✅ 选定 CLI 脚本）\n127: \n128: - **CLI 脚本**：简单直接，符合现有示例风格（`basic_usage.py`、`agent_runtime_usage.py`）\n129: - **FastAPI Web 服务**：功能更丰富，但引入额外依赖和复杂度\n130: - **决策**：保持 CLI 脚本形式，与现有示例矩阵一致\n131: \n132: ### 3. 内联代码 vs. 远程脚本文件（✅ 选定内联代码）\n133: \n134: - **内联代码**：通过 `run_code` 直接传递 Python 代码，无需额外文件管理\n135: - **远程脚本文件**：先 `write_file` 上传脚本再执行，步骤更多\n136: - **决策**：使用内联代码简化示例，展示 `run_code` 的直接用法\n137: \n138: ## Upstream Dependencies\n139: \n140: - `agentcube-sdk` `CodeInterpreterClient` 公开 API 稳定\n141: - 远程沙箱环境支持 Python 3.10+ 和 `pip install`\n142: \n143: ## Status\n144: \n145: - [ ] Proposal review\n146: - [ ] Implementation\n147: - [ ] Verification\n\n(End of file - total 147 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n\n**Module:** example\n**Language:** Python\n**Size:** M\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube Python SDK 提供一个 PCAP（Packet Capture）网络流量分析示例应用，展示如何使用 `CodeInterpreterClient` 在远程沙箱环境中完成文件上传、代码执行、结果下载的完整工作流。该示例覆盖 SDK 的核心 API（`upload_file`、`run_code`、`execute_command`、`download_file`、context manager 生命周期），为用户提供一个可运行的网络分析参考实现，降低 SDK 上手门槛。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **示例脚本** `examples/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n   - 环境变量配置（`ROUTER_URL`、`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`、`AUTH_TOKEN`）\n   - PCAP 文件上传至远程沙箱（`upload_file`）\n   - 使用 `run_code` 执行 Python 分析脚本（基于 `scapy` 库）：\n     - 协议分布统计（TCP/UDP/ICMP/HTTP/DNS 占比）\n     - Top N 源/目的 IP 地址","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775886220477,"end":1775886220490}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886221981,"sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","part":{"id":"prt_d7b113d2f001MVwb27LxZFru13","messageID":"msg_d7b1124fd001TMLIipQz14HW06","sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_71eb2b7633e64bf3865ac570","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers the PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application for the AgentCube Python SDK. It demonstrates the complete workflow of file upload, remote code execution, and result download using `CodeInterpreterClient`, providing users with a runnable network analysis reference implementation.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 System Context\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                         User / Developer                             │\n14: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n15: │  │              examples/pcap_analyzer/                         │    │\n16: │  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n17: │  │  │              pcap_analyzer.py                         │  │    │\n18: │  │  │         (CLI Example Script)                          │  │    │\n19: │  │  └──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n20: │  │                         │                                   │    │\n21: │  │  ┌──────────────────────▼───────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n22: │  │  │         CodeInterpreterClient (SDK)                   │  │    │\n23: │  │  │   (upload_file, run_code, execute_command,            │  │    │\n24: │  │  │    download_file, list_files, context manager)        │  │    │\n25: │  │  └──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n26: │  └─────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┘    │\n27: └────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────┘\n28:                              │\n29:                              ▼\n30: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n31: │                    AgentCube Platform                                │\n32: │  ┌──────────────────────┐          ┌────────────────────────────┐   │\n33: │  │  Control Plane       │◄────────►│  Code Interpreter Pod      │   │\n34: │  │  (Session Lifecycle) │         │  (Python 3.10+, scapy)     │   │\n35: │  └──────────────────────┘          └────────────────────────────┘   │\n36: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n40: \n41: - **Example-only**: No modifications to SDK core code; uses only public API (`__all__` exports)\n42: - **CLI script style**: Consistent with existing examples (`basic_usage.py`, `agent_runtime_usage.py`)\n43: - **Self-contained**: Single script with embedded analysis logic via `run_code`\n44: - **Graceful degradation**: `tshark` as optional enhancement with conditional detection\n45: - **Small footprint**: Sample PCAP < 1MB, no chunked upload complexity\n46: \n47: ### 1.4 Package Structure\n48: \n49: ```\n50: sdk-python/\n51: ├── examples/\n52: │   ├── basic_usage.py                      # Existing\n53: │   ├── agent_runtime_usage.py              # Existing\n54: │   └── pcap_analyzer/                      # NEW (this AR)\n55: │       ├── pcap_analyzer.py                # Main example script\n56: │       ├── README.md                       # Usage guide\n57: │       ├── requirements.txt                # Example dependencies\n58: │       └── sample_traffic.pcap             # Sample PCAP file (< 1MB)\n59: └── ...\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n63: \n64: | Dependency | Scope | Purpose |\n65: |------------|-------|---------|\n66: | `agentcube-sdk` | Local import | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n67: | `scapy` | Remote sandbox | PCAP parsing (installed via `run_code` if needed) |\n68: | `tshark` (optional) | Remote sandbox | CLI filtering tool (conditional detection) |\n69: \n70: **No new Python package dependencies** — the example script uses only stdlib + `agentcube-sdk`.\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 2. Data Structures\n75: \n76: ### 2.1 Analysis Result Format (JSON)\n77: \n78: The remote analysis script produces JSON output with the following structure:\n79: \n80: ```json\n81: {\n82:   \"file_name\": \"sample_traffic.pcap\",\n83:   \"total_packets\": 1234,\n84:   \"duration_seconds\": 60.5,\n85:   \"protocols\": {\n86:     \"TCP\": 800,\n87:     \"UDP\": 300,\n88:     \"ICMP\": 50,\n89:     \"HTTP\": 60,\n90:     \"DNS\": 24\n91:   },\n92:   \"top_source_ips\": [\n93:     {\"ip\": \"192.168.1.100\", \"count\": 500},\n94:     {\"ip\": \"10.0.0.1\", \"count\": 300}\n95:   ],\n96:   \"top_dest_ips\": [\n97:     {\"ip\": \"8.8.8.8\", \"count\": 200},\n98:     {\"ip\": \"1.1.1.1\", \"count\": 150}\n99:   ],\n100:   \"timeline\": [\n101:     {\"timestamp\": 1699000000.0, \"packets\": 100},\n102:     {\"timestamp\": 1699000010.0, \"packets\": 150}\n103:   ],\n104:   \"errors\": []\n105: }\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### 2.2 CLI Arguments\n109: \n110: | Argument | Type | Default | Description |\n111: |----------|------|---------|-------------|\n112: | `--pcap-file` | `str` | `sample_traffic.pcap` | Path to PCAP file to analyze |\n113: | `--output` | `str` | `analysis_result.json` | Local path for result output |\n114: | `--top-n` | `int` | `10` | Number of top IPs to report |\n115: | `--timeline-interval` | `float` | `10.0` | Timeline bucket size in seconds |\n116: | `--verbose` | `flag` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n117: \n118: ### 2.3 Environment Variables\n119: \n120: | Variable | Required | Description |\n121: |----------|----------|-------------|\n122: | `ROUTER_URL` | Yes | Router endpoint URL |\n123: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | No | Control plane URL (defaults to SDK default) |\n124: | `AUTH_TOKEN` | No | Auth token (falls back to SA token file) |\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 3. Interfaces\n129: \n130: ### 3.1 Main Script Entry Point\n131: \n132: ```python\n133: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n134: \"\"\"PCAP Analyzer Example — demonstrates CodeInterpreterClient workflow.\"\"\"\n135: \n136: import argparse\n137: import json\n138: import os\n139: import sys\n140: \n141: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n142: \n143: \n144: def main():\n145:     parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"PCAP Analyzer Example\")\n146:     parser.add_argument(\"--pcap-file\", default=\"sample_traffic.pcap\")\n147:     parser.add_argument(\"--output\", default=\"analysis_result.json\")\n148:     parser.add_argument(\"--top-n\", type=int, default=10)\n149:     parser.add_argument(\"--timeline-interval\", type=float, default=10.0)\n150:     parser.add_argument(\"--verbose\", action=\"store_true\")\n151:     args = parser.parse_args()\n152: \n153:     router_url = os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n154:     if not router_url:\n155:         print(\"Error: ROUTER_URL environment variable is required\", file=sys.stderr)\n156:         sys.exit(1)\n157: \n158:     analyze_pcap(\n159:         pcap_file=args.pcap_file,\n160:         output_file=args.output,\n161:         top_n=args.top_n,\n162:         timeline_interval=args.timeline_interval,\n163:         verbose=args.verbose,\n164:         router_url=router_url,\n165:     )\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### 3.2 Core Analysis Function\n169: \n170: ```python\n171: def analyze_pcap(\n172:     pcap_file: str,\n173:     output_file: str,\n174:     top_n: int,\n175:     timeline_interval: float,\n176:     verbose: bool,\n177:     router_url: str,\n178: ) -> None:\n179:     \"\"\"Upload PCAP, run analysis, download results.\"\"\"\n180: ```\n181: \n182: **Workflow:**\n183: \n184: 1. Validate PCAP file exists locally\n185: 2. Create `CodeInterpreterClient` (context manager)\n186: 3. Upload PCAP file to remote sandbox (`upload_file`)\n187: 4. Install `scapy` if needed (`run_code` with `pip install`)\n188: 5. Execute analysis script (`run_code` with embedded Python)\n189: 6. Optionally run `tshark` commands (`execute_command` if available)\n190: 7. Write results to remote file (`write_file` or script output)\n191: 8. Download results (`download_file`)\n192: 9. Print summary to console\n193: 10. Context manager cleanup (`__exit__` → `stop()`)\n194: \n195: ### 3.3 Embedded Analysis Script (via `run_code`)\n196: \n197: The analysis logic is passed as a Python string to `run_code`. It uses `scapy` to parse the PCAP file:\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: ANALYSIS_SCRIPT = \"\"\"\n201: from scapy.all import rdpcap, IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, DNS, Raw\n202: import json\n203: import sys\n204: from collections import Counter\n205: \n206: def analyze_pcap(pcap_path, top_n=10, timeline_interval=10.0):\n207:     packets = rdpcap(pcap_path)\n208:     \n209:     result = {\n210:         \"file_name\": pcap_path,\n211:         \"total_packets\": len(packets),\n212:         \"duration_seconds\": 0.0,\n213:         \"protocols\": {},\n214:         \"top_source_ips\": [],\n215:         \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n216:         \"timeline\": [],\n217:         \"errors\": []\n218:     }\n219:     \n220:     if not packets:\n221:         return result\n222:     \n223:     # Duration\n224:     first_ts = float(packets[0].time)\n225:     last_ts = float(packets[-1].time)\n226:     result[\"duration_seconds\"] = last_ts - first_ts\n227:     \n228:     # Protocol distribution\n229:     proto_counts = Counter()\n230:     src_ips = Counter()\n231:     dst_ips = Counter()\n232:     timeline_buckets = Counter()\n233:     \n234:     for pkt in packets:\n235:         ts = float(pkt.time)\n236:         bucket = int((ts - first_ts) / timeline_interval) * timeline_interval + first_ts\n237:         \n238:         if pkt.haslayer(TCP):\n239:             proto_counts[\"TCP\"] += 1\n240:             if pkt.haslayer(Raw):\n241:                 proto_counts[\"HTTP\"] += 1  # Simplified HTTP detection\n242:         elif pkt.haslayer(UDP):\n243:             if pkt.haslayer(DNS):\n244:                 proto_counts[\"DNS\"] += 1\n245:             else:\n246:                 proto_counts[\"UDP\"] += 1\n247:         elif pkt.haslayer(ICMP):\n248:             proto_counts[\"ICMP\"] += 1\n249:         else:\n250:             proto_counts[\"Other\"] += 1\n251:         \n252:         if pkt.haslayer(IP):\n253:             src_ips[pkt[IP].src] += 1\n254:             dst_ips[pkt[IP].dst] += 1\n255:         \n256:         timeline_buckets[bucket] += 1\n257:     \n258:     result[\"protocols\"] = dict(proto_counts)\n259:     result[\"top_source_ips\"] = [\n260:         {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n261:         for ip, count in src_ips.most_common(top_n)\n262:     ]\n263:     result[\"top_dest_ips\"] = [\n264:         {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n265:         for ip, count in dst_ips.most_common(top_n)\n266:     ]\n267:     result[\"timeline\"] = sorted([\n268:         {\"timestamp\": ts, \"packets\": count}\n269:         for ts, count in timeline_buckets.items()\n270:     ], key=lambda x: x[\"timestamp\"])\n271:     \n272:     return result\n273: \n274: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n275:     pcap_file = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else \"/tmp/uploaded.pcap\"\n276:     top_n = int(sys.argv[2]) if len(sys.argv) > 2 else 10\n277:     interval = float(sys.argv[3]) if len(sys.argv) > 3 else 10.0\n278:     \n279:     result = analyze_pcap(pcap_file, top_n, interval)\n280:     print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n281: \"\"\"\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ### 3.4 Optional tshark Enhancement\n285: \n286: ```python\n287: def check_tshark_available(client: CodeInterpreterClient) -> bool:\n288:     \"\"\"Check if tshark is available in the remote sandbox.\"\"\"\n289:     try:\n290:         result = client.execute_command(\"which tshark\")\n291:         return result.strip() != \"\"\n292:     except Exception:\n293:         return False\n294: \n295: \n296: def run_tshark_filter(client: CodeInterpreterClient, pcap_path: str, filter_expr: str) -> str:\n297:     \"\"\"Run tshark with a display filter on the remote PCAP.\"\"\"\n298:     cmd = f\"tshark -r {pcap_path} -Y '{filter_expr}' -T fields -e ip.src -e ip.dst -e frame.len\"\n299:     return client.execute_command(cmd)\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## 4. Error Handling\n305: \n306: ### 4.1 Error Classification\n307: \n308: | Scenario | Exception | Handling |\n309: |----------|-----------|----------|\n310: | PCAP file not found locally | `FileNotFoundError` | Print error, exit 1 |\n311: | `ROUTER_URL` not set | `ValueError` | Print error, exit 1 |\n312: | Upload failure | SDK exception | Propagate with context |\n313: | `scapy` installation failure | `CommandExecutionError` | Retry or warn, continue |\n314: | Analysis script error | `CommandExecutionError` | Print stderr, exit 1 |\n315: | Result download failure | SDK exception | Propagate with context |\n316: | Invalid JSON output | `json.JSONDecodeError` | Print raw output, warn |\n317: | Context manager cleanup failure | SDK exception | Log warning, exit |\n318: \n319: ### 4.2 Error Recovery Strategy\n320: \n321: ```python\n322: def analyze_pcap(...):\n323:     # Pre-flight checks\n324:     if not os.path.exists(pcap_file):\n325:         print(f\"Error: PCAP file not found: {pcap_file}\", file=sys.stderr)\n326:         sys.exit(1)\n327:     \n328:     # Context manager ensures cleanup\n329:     with CodeInterpreterClient(\n330:         name=\"pcap-analyzer\",\n331:         router_url=router_url,\n332:         verbose=verbose,\n333:     ) as client:\n334:         try:\n335:             # Upload\n336:             remote_path = f\"/tmp/{os.path.basename(pcap_file)}\"\n337:             client.upload_file(pcap_file, remote_path)\n338:             \n339:             # Install scapy (best effort)\n340:             try:\n341:                 client.run_code(\"python\", \"import scapy\")\n342:             except Exception:\n343:                 if verbose:\n344:                     print(\"Installing scapy in remote sandbox...\")\n345:                 client.run_code(\"python\", \"import subprocess; subprocess.run(['pip', 'install', 'scapy'])\")\n346:             \n347:             # Run analysis\n348:             script = ANALYSIS_SCRIPT.replace(\"TOP_N_PLACEHOLDER\", str(top_n))\n349:             result_json = client.run_code(\"python\", script)\n350:             result = json.loads(result_json)\n351:             \n352:             # Optional tshark\n353:             if check_tshark_available(client):\n354:                 tshark_result = run_tshark_filter(client, remote_path, \"tcp\")\n355:                 result[\"tshark_tcp_summary\"] = tshark_result\n356:             \n357:             # Save results locally\n358:             with open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n359:                 json.dump(result, f, indent=2)\n360:             \n361:             # Print summary\n362:             print_analysis_summary(result)\n363:             \n364:         except Exception as e:\n365:             print(f\"Analysis failed: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n366:             sys.exit(1)\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## 5. Implementation Notes\n372: \n373: ### 5.1 Remote Sandbox Assumptions\n374: \n375: | Assumption | Verification | Fallback |\n376: |------------|--------------|----------|\n377: | Python 3.10+ available | `run_code(\"python\", \"import sys; print(sys.version)\")` | Error if not met |\n378: | `pip install` works | Try `pip install scapy` | Pre-install in sandbox image |\n379: | `/tmp` writable | `execute_command(\"touch /tmp/test && rm /tmp/test\")` | Use alternative path |\n380: | `tshark` available (optional) | `execute_command(\"which tshark\")` | Skip tshark features |\n381: \n382: ### 5.2 Script Size Considerations\n383: \n384: The embedded `ANALYSIS_SCRIPT` is ~60 lines of Python. For `run_code`, this is passed as a string argument. If the script grows significantly, consider:\n385: \n386: 1. Using `write_file` to upload the script first, then `execute_command` to run it\n387: 2. Splitting into multiple `run_code` calls\n388: \n389: Current approach (inline) is preferred for simplicity and demonstration purposes.\n390: \n391: ### 5.3 Timeout Configuration\n392: \n393: | Operation | Timeout | Rationale |\n394: |-----------|---------|-----------|\n395: | PCAP upload | Default (120s) | < 1MB file, should be fast |\n396: | scapy install | 60s | Network-dependent |\n397: | Analysis execution | 120s | Depends on PCAP size |\n398: | tshark filter | 60s | Optional enhancement |\n399: | Result download | Default (120s) | JSON output, small |\n400: \n401: ### 5.4 Sample PCAP Generation\n402: \n403: The `sample_traffic.pcap` file can be generated using `scapy`:\n404: \n405: ```python\n406: # scripts/generate_sample_pcap.py\n407: from scapy.all import IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, wrpcap, Ether\n408: import random\n409: \n410: packets = []\n411: base_time = 1699000000.0\n412: \n413: for i in range(100):\n414:     src = f\"192.168.1.{random.randint(1, 254)}\"\n415:     dst = f\"10.0.0.{random.randint(1, 254)}\"\n416:     \n417:     if i % 3 == 0:\n418:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / TCP(sport=random.randint(1024, 65535), dport=80)\n419:     elif i % 3 == 1:\n420:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / UDP(sport=53, dport=random.randint(1024, 65535))\n421:     else:\n422:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / ICMP()\n423:     \n424:     pkt.time = base_time + i * 0.5\n425:     packets.append(pkt)\n426: \n427: wrpcap(\"sample_traffic.pcap\", packets)\n428: ```\n429: \n430: ---\n431: \n432: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n433: \n434: ### 6.1 Test Categories\n435: \n436: | Category | Scope | Approach |\n437: |----------|-------|----------|\n438: | Script validation | Syntax, imports | `python -m py_compile pcap_analyzer.py` |\n439: | Unit tests | Analysis logic | Run embedded script locally with test PCAP |\n440: | Integration tests | SDK interaction | Mock `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n441: | Manual E2E | Full workflow | Run against real AgentCube platform |\n442: \n443: ### 6.2 Key Test Scenarios\n444: \n445: | Test Name | Description |\n446: |-----------|-------------|\n447: | `test_script_syntax` | Embedded analysis script compiles without errors |\n448: | `test_analysis_with_sample_pcap` | Run analysis on sample_traffic.pcap, verify JSON structure |\n449: | `test_empty_pcap` | Handle PCAP with 0 packets gracefully |\n450: | `test_cli_argument_parsing` | Verify argparse handles all flags correctly |\n451: | `test_missing_router_url` | Exit with error if ROUTER_URL not set |\n452: | `test_missing_pcap_file` | Exit with error if PCAP file not found |\n453: | `test_mocked_sdk_workflow` | Mock CodeInterpreterClient, verify call sequence |\n454: \n455: ### 6.3 Mocked SDK Test Example\n456: \n457: ```python\n458: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n459: \n460: def test_mocked_sdk_workflow():\n461:     \"\"\"Verify the expected SDK call sequence.\"\"\"\n462:     mock_client = MagicMock()\n463:     mock_client.__enter__ = MagicMock(return_value=mock_client)\n464:     mock_client.__exit__ = MagicMock(return_value=False)\n465:     \n466:     mock_client.run_code.return_value = json.dumps({\n467:         \"total_packets\": 100,\n468:         \"protocols\": {\"TCP\": 60, \"UDP\": 40},\n469:         \"top_source_ips\": [],\n470:         \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n471:         \"timeline\": [],\n472:         \"errors\": []\n473:     })\n474:     \n475:     with patch(\"agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient\", return_value=mock_client):\n476:         # Run analyze_pcap with test fixtures\n477:         # Verify call sequence:\n478:         # 1. upload_file called\n479:         # 2. run_code called for analysis\n480:         # 3. download_file or result handling\n481:         pass\n482: ```\n483: \n484: ---\n485: \n486: ## 7. Usage Examples\n487: \n488: ### 7.1 Basic Usage\n489: \n490: ```bash\n491: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\n492: cd examples/pcap_analyzer\n493: python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap\n494: ```\n495: \n496: **Expected output:**\n497: \n498: ```\n499: PCAP Analysis Complete\n500: =====================\n501: File: sample_traffic.pcap\n502: Total packets: 100\n503: Duration: 49.50s\n504: \n505: Protocol Distribution:\n506:   TCP:  60 (60.0%)\n507:   UDP:  40 (40.0%)\n508: \n509: Top Source IPs:\n510:   192.168.1.105: 15 packets\n511:   192.168.1.200: 12 packets\n512:   192.168.1.50:  10 packets\n513: \n514: Top Destination IPs:\n515:   10.0.0.1: 25 packets\n516:   10.0.0.5: 20 packets\n517: \n518: Results saved to: analysis_result.json\n519: ```\n520: \n521: ### 7.2 Custom Parameters\n522: \n523: ```bash\n524: python pcap_analyzer.py \\\n525:   --pcap-file /path/to/capture.pcap \\\n526:   --output /path/to/report.json \\\n527:   --top-n 20 \\\n528:   --timeline-interval 5.0 \\\n529:   --verbose\n530: ```\n531: \n532: ### 7.3 With tshark (if available)\n533: \n534: When `tshark` is detected in the remote sandbox, additional filtering output is included:\n535: \n536: ```\n537: tshark TCP Filter Results:\n538:   192.168.1.100 -> 10.0.0.1: 1500 bytes\n539:   192.168.1.100 -> 10.0.0.1: 1200 bytes\n540:   ...\n541: ```\n542: \n543: ---\n544: \n545: ## 8. README Content\n546: \n547: The `examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md` will contain:\n548: \n549: ```markdown\n550: # PCAP Analyzer Example\n551: \n552: Demonstrates the complete CodeInterpreterClient workflow:\n553: upload → analyze → download.\n554: \n555: ## Prerequisites\n556: \n557: - Python 3.10+\n558: - `agentcube-sdk` installed\n559: - Access to AgentCube platform (ROUTER_URL)\n560: \n561: ## Quick Start\n562: \n563: ```bash\n564: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\n565: python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap\n566: ```\n567: \n568: ## Analysis Features\n569: \n570: - Protocol distribution (TCP/UDP/ICMP/DNS/HTTP)\n571: - Top N source and destination IPs\n572: - Traffic timeline overview\n573: - Optional tshark filtering (if available in sandbox)\n574: \n575: ## Output\n576: \n577: Results are saved as JSON and printed as a summary to stdout.\n578: ```\n\n(End of file - total 578 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers the PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application for the AgentCube Python SDK. It demonstrates the complete workflow of file upload, remote code execution, and result download using `CodeInterpreterClient`, providing users with a runnable network analysis reference implementation.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User / Developer                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │              examples/pcap_analyzer/                         │    │\n│  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n│  │  │              pcap_analyzer.py                         │  │    │\n│  │  │         (CLI Example Script)                          │  │    │\n│  │  └──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n│  │                         │                                   │    │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md","time":{"start":1775886221962,"end":1775886221978}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886222983,"sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1142f500160C20FSpX63Bc2","messageID":"msg_d7b1124fd001TMLIipQz14HW06","sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0a3d2bc6e1344134a09567ce","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 — Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `example` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n4: **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n5: **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## T-1: Project scaffolding — `examples/pcap_analyzer/` directory structure\n10: \n11: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/` directory\n12: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/__init__.py` (empty, marks package)\n13: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/requirements.txt` with `agentcube-sdk` and `scapy`\n14: - [ ] Verify directory structure matches design spec\n15: \n16: ## T-2: CLI argument parser (`argparse`)\n17: \n18: - [ ] Implement `parse_args()` function with arguments:\n19:   - `--pcap-file` (str, default `sample_traffic.pcap`)\n20:   - `--output` (str, default `analysis_result.json`)\n21:   - `--top-n` (int, default `10`)\n22:   - `--timeline-interval` (float, default `10.0`)\n23:   - `--verbose` (flag, default `False`)\n24: - [ ] Validate `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set; print error and `sys.exit(1)` if missing\n25: - [ ] Write test: all arguments parsed with defaults\n26: - [ ] Write test: explicit arguments override defaults\n27: - [ ] Write test: missing `ROUTER_URL` → error message to stderr, exit code 1\n28: \n29: ## T-3: Pre-flight validation helpers\n30: \n31: - [ ] Implement `validate_pcap_file(pcap_file: str) -> None` — raises `FileNotFoundError` if file does not exist\n32: - [ ] Implement `check_python_version() -> None` — verifies Python 3.10+ via `sys.version_info`\n33: - [ ] Write test: valid PCAP path passes validation\n34: - [ ] Write test: nonexistent PCAP path raises `FileNotFoundError` with descriptive message\n35: - [ ] Write test: Python < 3.10 raises error\n36: \n37: ## T-4: Embedded analysis script (`ANALYSIS_SCRIPT`)\n38: \n39: - [ ] Define `ANALYSIS_SCRIPT` constant — Python string using `scapy.all` (`rdpcap`, `IP`, `TCP`, `UDP`, `ICMP`, `DNS`, `Raw`)\n40: - [ ] Implement `analyze_pcap(pcap_path, top_n, timeline_interval)` function inside the script:\n41:   - Parse packets with `rdpcap`\n42:   - Calculate `duration_seconds` from first/last packet timestamps\n43:   - Count protocol distribution (TCP, UDP, ICMP, DNS, HTTP via `Raw` layer)\n44:   - Compute top N source/destination IPs using `collections.Counter`\n45:   - Build timeline buckets grouped by `timeline_interval`\n46:   - Return JSON-serializable dict matching design spec format\n47: - [ ] Handle empty PCAP (0 packets) gracefully — return result with zero counts\n48: - [ ] Write test: embedded script syntax compiles (`py_compile`)\n49: - [ ] Write test: run embedded script locally against a test PCAP, verify JSON structure has all required keys\n50: \n51: ## T-5: `check_tshark_available` helper\n52: \n53: - [ ] Implement `check_tshark_available(client: CodeInterpreterClient) -> bool`\n54: - [ ] Use `client.execute_command(\"which tshark\")` — return `True` if non-empty output, `False` on exception\n55: - [ ] Write test: mocked client returns `True` when `which tshark` succeeds\n56: - [ ] Write test: mocked client returns `False` when command raises exception\n57: \n58: ## T-6: `run_tshark_filter` helper\n59: \n60: - [ ] Implement `run_tshark_filter(client, pcap_path, filter_expr) -> str`\n61: - [ ] Construct command: `tshark -r {pcap_path} -Y '{filter_expr}' -T fields -e ip.src -e ip.dst -e frame.len`\n62: - [ ] Return `client.execute_command(cmd)` output\n63: - [ ] Write test: mocked client returns tshark output string\n64: \n65: ## T-7: `print_analysis_summary` output formatter\n66: \n67: - [ ] Implement `print_analysis_summary(result: dict) -> None` that prints:\n68:   - Header: \"PCAP Analysis Complete\" with separator\n69:   - File name, total packets, duration\n70:   - Protocol distribution with counts and percentages\n71:   - Top N source IPs with packet counts\n72:   - Top N destination IPs with packet counts\n73:   - Result file path\n74: - [ ] Write test: captures stdout, verifies formatted output contains all sections\n75: - [ ] Write test: handles empty protocols dict gracefully\n76: \n77: ## T-8: Core `analyze_pcap` orchestration function\n78: \n79: - [ ] Implement `analyze_pcap(pcap_file, output_file, top_n, timeline_interval, verbose, router_url) -> None`:\n80:   1. Validate PCAP file exists locally\n81:   2. Enter `CodeInterpreterClient` context manager with `name=\"pcap-analyzer\"`, `router_url`, `verbose`\n82:   3. Upload PCAP: `client.upload_file(pcap_file, f\"/tmp/{os.path.basename(pcap_file)}\")`\n83:   4. Best-effort scapy install: try `import scapy`, fall back to `pip install scapy` via `run_code`\n84:   5. Execute analysis: `client.run_code(\"python\", ANALYSIS_SCRIPT)` with parameters\n85:   6. Parse JSON result from `run_code` output\n86:   7. If `check_tshark_available(client)`, run `run_tshark_filter` and attach to result\n87:   8. Write result JSON to `output_file` locally\n88:   9. Call `print_analysis_summary(result)`\n89: - [ ] Wrap in try/except — print `Analysis failed: {e}` to stderr, `sys.exit(1)` on failure\n90: - [ ] Write test: mocked `CodeInterpreterClient` verifies full call sequence (upload → run_code scapy check → run_code analysis → file write → summary)\n91: - [ ] Write test: scapy already installed skips `pip install`\n92: - [ ] Write test: scapy not installed triggers `pip install`\n93: - [ ] Write test: tshark available → additional `execute_command` and `run_tshark_filter` called\n94: - [ ] Write test: tshark not available → skips tshark steps\n95: - [ ] Write test: `run_code` raises exception → error printed, exit 1\n96: - [ ] Write test: context manager `__exit__` called even on exception (cleanup guarantee)\n97: \n98: ## T-9: `main()` entry point\n99: \n100: - [ ] Implement `main()` function:\n101:   - Call `parse_args()` to get CLI arguments\n102:   - Resolve `ROUTER_URL` from environment\n103:   - Call `analyze_pcap()` with parsed args and router URL\n104: - [ ] Add `if __name__ == \"__main__\": main()` guard\n105: - [ ] Write test: end-to-end with all mocks — verifies `main()` calls `analyze_pcap` with correct args\n106: - [ ] Write test: `--verbose` flag passed through to `analyze_pcap`\n107: \n108: ## T-10: Sample PCAP generation script\n109: \n110: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/generate_sample.py` script using `scapy.all` (`IP`, `TCP`, `UDP`, `ICMP`, `wrpcap`, `Ether`)\n111: - [ ] Generate 100 packets with mixed protocols (TCP/UDP/ICMP), random IPs, staggered timestamps\n112: - [ ] Output `sample_traffic.pcap` (< 1MB) to current directory\n113: - [ ] Run script to produce `examples/pcap_analyzer/sample_traffic.pcap`\n114: - [ ] Write test: generated PCAP file exists and is < 1MB\n115: - [ ] Write test: generated PCAP contains at least TCP, UDP, and ICMP packets\n116: \n117: ## T-11: `README.md` documentation\n118: \n119: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md` with:\n120:   - Prerequisites (Python 3.10+, `agentcube-sdk`, `ROUTER_URL`)\n121:   - Quick Start command\n122:   - Analysis features list (protocol distribution, top IPs, timeline, tshark)\n123:   - CLI arguments table\n124:   - Expected output example\n125:   - Output format description (JSON + stdout summary)\n126: \n127: ## T-12: Integration tests — mocked SDK workflow\n128: \n129: - [ ] Write integration test: full workflow with `unittest.mock.patch` on `CodeInterpreterClient`\n130:   - Verify `upload_file` called with correct paths\n131:   - Verify `run_code` called for scapy check and analysis\n132:   - Verify result JSON written to output file\n133:   - Verify `print_analysis_summary` called\n134: - [ ] Write integration test: empty PCAP handling (mock returns 0 packets)\n135: - [ ] Write integration test: `CommandExecutionError` during analysis → proper error handling\n136: \n137: ## T-13: Lint, type-check, and manual verification\n138: \n139: - [ ] `python -m py_compile examples/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` — no syntax errors\n140: - [ ] `python -m py_compile examples/pcap_analyzer/generate_sample.py` — no syntax errors\n141: - [ ] `pytest examples/pcap_analyzer/tests/ -v` — all tests pass\n142: - [ ] Manual E2E: run `python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap` against real AgentCube platform (if available)\n143: - [ ] Verify `analysis_result.json` output matches design spec JSON schema\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## Dependency Graph\n148: \n149: ```\n150: T-1 ──┬── T-2 ── T-9\n151:       │\n152:       ├── T-3 ── T-8\n153:       │\n154:       ├── T-4 ── T-8\n155:       │\n156:       ├── T-5 ── T-8\n157:       │\n158:       ├── T-6 ── T-8\n159:       │\n160:       ├── T-7 ── T-8\n161:       │\n162:       ├── T-10\n163:       │\n164:       └── T-11\n165: \n166: T-8 ── T-12\n167: \n168: T-12 ── T-13\n169: T-10 ── T-13\n170: T-11 ── T-13\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ## Parallelizable Groups\n174: \n175: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n176: |-------|-------|---------------|\n177: | G1 | T-1 | None |\n178: | G2 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5, T-6, T-7, T-10, T-11 | T-1 |\n179: | G3 | T-8 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5, T-6, T-7 |\n180: | G4 | T-9 | T-2, T-8 |\n181: | G5 | T-12 | T-8 |\n182: | G6 | T-13 | T-9, T-10, T-11, T-12 |\n\n(End of file - total 182 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 — Tasks\n\n**Module:** `example` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `pyt