{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886263373,"sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","part":{"id":"prt_d7b119c7a001CYN4UfjssEwdAV","messageID":"msg_d7b11954d001wy52dFc3JzsZe3","sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_8cc6b5b69b344c17abca2543","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** L\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 `pkg/workloadmanager` 模块编写全面的 Go 单元测试，覆盖 handler、middleware、reconciler、response 子包及顶层常量定义，提升代码质量、防止回归、并为后续重构提供安全网。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **handler/** — HTTP handler 单元测试（路由处理、请求解析、响应构造、错误处理）\n2. **middleware/** — 中间件单元测试（认证、日志、请求校验、recovery）\n3. **reconciler/** — 协调器单元测试（状态同步、重试逻辑、幂等操作）\n4. **response/** — 响应工具单元测试（JSON 序列化、错误码映射、HTTP 状态码）\n5. **const.go** — 常量验证测试（枚举值完整性、边界条件）\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- 集成测试（需要真实外部依赖）\n- E2E 测试（需要完整平台环境）\n- 性能/基准测试（后续单独 AR）\n- 修改 workloadmanager 生产代码（仅新增 `*_test.go` 文件）\n\n## Architecture Summary\n\n### Current State\n\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/` 包含 handler、middleware、reconciler、response 子包\n- 缺少系统化的单元测试覆盖\n- 各子包之间存在依赖关系（handler → middleware → response，reconciler 独立）\n\n### Target State\n\n每个子包新增对应的 `*_test.go` 文件，覆盖正常路径、边界条件、错误路径。\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| 依赖 | 来源 | 说明 |\n|------|------|------|\n| `testing` | Go stdlib | 标准测试框架 |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | go.mod | 断言库（如项目已使用） |\n| `net/http/httptest` | Go stdlib | HTTP handler 测试 |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| 文件/目录 | 状态 | 说明 |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/**/*_test.go` | 新增 | 各子包单元测试 |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/` | 无变更 | 生产代码不修改 |\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n|------|------|----------|\n| 内部未导出函数无法直接测试 | 中 | 通过公开 API 间接测试，或使用 `internal_test` 包 |\n| 外部依赖（数据库、HTTP 客户端）难以 mock | 中 | 使用 interface 抽象 + mock 实现 |\n| 测试数据构造复杂 | 低 | 使用 test fixtures / table-driven tests |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Table-driven tests vs. individual test functions（✅ 选定 table-driven）\n\n- **Table-driven**：Go 惯用法，易于扩展，减少样板代码\n- **Individual functions**：每个场景独立函数，更清晰但冗余\n- **决策**：以 table-driven 为主，复杂场景辅以独立函数\n\n### 2. testify vs. 标准库（✅ 选定 testify，如项目已使用）\n\n- **testify**：丰富的断言、mock 支持\n- **标准库**：零依赖，但断言需手动实现\n- **决策**：跟随项目现有测试风格\n\n## Upstream Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/` 生产代码稳定\n- Go 测试工具链可用（`go test`）\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Proposal review\n- [ ] Implementation\n- [ ] Verification\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775886263359,"end":1775886263371}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886289262,"sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","part":{"id":"prt_d7b11e4ac001dZIssOQZDkt5r7","messageID":"msg_d7b11954d001wy52dFc3JzsZe3","sessionID":"ses_284eeec8fffeL0qQ1Qc24O23Ng","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_31c53bf4715e400ca5467a00","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-038: Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers comprehensive Go unit tests for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module, including handler, middleware, reconciler, response sub-packages and top-level constants.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── const.go              # Constants/enums\n├── const_test.go         # NEW — constant validation tests\n├── handler/\n│   ├── *.go              # HTTP handlers\n│   └── *_test.go         # NEW — handler tests\n├── middleware/\n│   ├── *.go              # HTTP middleware\n│   └── *_test.go         # NEW — middleware tests\n├── reconciler/\n│   ├── *.go              # State reconciler\n│   └── *_test.go         # NEW — reconciler tests\n└── response/\n    ├── *.go              # Response utilities\n    └── *_test.go         # NEW — response tests\n```\n\n### 1.3 Design Principles\n\n- **Table-driven tests**: Go idiom for test data organization\n- **No production code changes**: Only `*_test.go` additions\n- **httptest for handlers**: `net/http/httptest` for HTTP handler testing\n- **Interface-based mocking**: Abstract external dependencies behind interfaces\n- **Black-box + white-box**: Mix of `package_test` and `package_internal_test` as needed\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test Strategy by Sub-Package\n\n### 2.1 handler/\n\n| Test Category | Approach |\n|---------------|----------|\n| Request parsing | Valid/invalid JSON, missing fields, type mismatches |\n| Response construction | Status codes, body format, headers |\n| Error handling | 4xx/5xx scenarios, panic recovery |\n| Edge cases | Empty body, oversized payload, concurrent requests |\n\n### 2.2 middleware/\n\n| Test Category | Approach |\n|---------------|----------|\n| Auth middleware | Valid token, expired token, missing token, malformed token |\n| Logging middleware | Output capture, request ID propagation |\n| Validation middleware | Pass-through, rejection with error response |\n| Recovery middleware | Panic caught, 500 returned, stack trace logged |\n\n### 2.3 reconciler/\n\n| Test Category | Approach |\n|---------------|----------|\n| State sync | Current vs desired state convergence |\n| Retry logic | Max retries, backoff, success after retry |\n| Idempotency | Repeated calls produce same result |\n| Error propagation | Dependency failure handling |\n\n### 2.4 response/\n\n| Test Category | Approach |\n|---------------|----------|\n| JSON serialization | Struct → JSON, nil fields, special characters |\n| Error code mapping | Internal error → HTTP status, custom codes |\n| Helper functions | Response writers, header setting |\n\n### 2.5 const.go\n\n| Test Category | Approach |\n|---------------|----------|\n| Enum completeness | All expected values present |\n| Boundary conditions | Min/max values, zero values |\n| String representations | `String()` methods (if any) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Testing Patterns\n\n### 3.1 Table-Driven Test Template\n\n```go\nfunc TestHandler_Foo(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name       string\n        input      RequestType\n        wantStatus int\n        wantBody   string\n        wantErr    bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name:       \"valid request\",\n            input:      RequestType{Field: \"value\"},\n            wantStatus: http.StatusOK,\n            wantBody:   `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`,\n            wantErr:    false,\n        },\n        {\n            name:       \"invalid request\",\n            input:      RequestType{},\n            wantStatus: http.StatusBadRequest,\n            wantBody:   `{\"error\":\"...\"}`,\n            wantErr:    true,\n        },\n    }\n\n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            // Arrange\n            req := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodPost, \"/path\", toJSON(tt.input))\n            w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n\n            // Act\n            handler(w, req)\n\n            // Assert\n            assert.Equal(t, tt.wantStatus, w.Code)\n            if tt.wantBody != \"\" {\n                assert.JSONEq(t, tt.wantBody, w.Body.String())\n            }\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Mock Pattern\n\n```go\ntype mockDependency struct {\n    // Record calls\n    calls []string\n    // Configure behavior\n    err error\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockDependency) DoSomething() error {\n    m.calls = append(m.calls, \"DoSomething\")\n    return m.err\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Coverage Targets\n\n| Sub-Package | Target Coverage | Rationale |\n|-------------|-----------------|-----------|\n| handler/ | 80%+ | Core user-facing logic |\n| middleware/ | 85%+ | Critical path, many edge cases |\n| reconciler/ | 75%+ | Complex state machine |\n| response/ | 90%+ | Simple utilities, should be fully covered |\n| const.go | 100% | Trivial but important |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Implementation Notes\n\n- Use `go test -cover` to measure coverage\n- Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` to execute all tests\n- No external services required — all dependencies mocked\n- Tests should be deterministic (no flaky tests)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/design.md","time":{"start":1775886289252,"end":1775886289260}}}}
